OL,3,CFamily 'terrified' as couple held in
OL,4,CIran face verdict within days
OL,6,FA spokesperson for the FCDO said: "We
OL,7,Fare deeply concerned by reports that
OL,8,FCraig and Lindsay Foreman have been
OL,9,Fcharged with espionage in Iran. We
OL,10,Fcontinue to raise this case directly
OL,11,Fwith the Iranian authorities.
OL,13,F"The FCDO are providing them with
OL,14,Fconsular assistance and remain in
OL,15,Fclose contact with their family
OL,16,Fmembers."
OL,18,FThe FCDO warns all British and British-
OL,19,FIranian nationals not to travel to
OL,20,FIran because of a "significant risk of
OL,21,Farrest, questioning or detention".
